Backend linting using Flake8 or Black
Security checks integrated (dependency vulnerability scan)
Pipeline fails if critical issues are detected

name: DEVOPS-01: CI/CD Pipeline Setup for Frontend and Backend
text_content:
Description
 Set up a CI/CD pipeline to automate build, test, and deployment processes for React frontend and Python backend applications.
Acceptance Criteria
Pipeline configured using GitHub Actions / GitLab CI / Jenkins
Separate stages for:
Code checkout
Dependency installation
Unit testing (FE & BE)
Build
Pipeline fails on test failure
Test coverage report generated
Pipeline triggers on pull requests and main branch commits

name: BE-01: Login API (User & Admin)
text_content:
Description
 Implement an authentication API for users and admins with role-based access.
Acceptance Criteria
POST /api/login endpoint implemented
Validates email/username and password
Returns JWT access token on success
Returns role (Admin/User) in response
Returns proper error messages for invalid credentials
Passwords stored using secure hashing
